Interface MediaService


  • public interface MediaService

      void upload(retrofit.mime.TypedFile media, retrofit.mime.TypedFile mediaData, retrofit.mime.TypedString additionalOwners, Callback<Media> cb)
      Uploads media (images) to Twitter for use in a Tweet or Twitter-hosted Card.

    • Method Detail

      • upload

        @Multipart
@POST(value="/1.1/media/upload.json")
void upload(@Part(value="media")
                         retrofit.mime.TypedFile media,
                         @Part(value="media_data")
                         retrofit.mime.TypedFile mediaData,
                         @Part(value="additional_owners")
                         retrofit.mime.TypedString additionalOwners,
                         Callback<Media> cb)
        Uploads media (images) to Twitter for use in a Tweet or Twitter-hosted Card. You may upload the raw binary file or its base64 encoded contents. The media and media_data parameters are mutually exclusive. Media uploads for images are limited to 5MB in file size. Supported MIME-types are PNG, JPEG, BMP, WEBP, GIF, and Animated Gif
        Parameters:
        media - the raw binary file content to upload. Cannot be used with the mediaData parameter.
        mediaData - the base64-encoded file content to upload. Cannot be used with the media parameter
        cb - The callback to invoke when the request completes.
